1) To be able to use AutoML Vision API, one has to follow the steps here:
   https://cloud.google.com/vision/automl/docs/tutorial.

2) For viewing camera streams on Linux:
   sudo apt-get install guvcview

3) To record camera streams on Linux:
   sudo apt-get install streamer

4) Python libraries that need to be installed: cv2, matplotlib.

Run ./run.sh to test the MHI-based system with live recordings.
Run python3 full_system.py $video_name to test the system on pre-recorded 
videos.
